dialog.text: Wake up, Dungeon Dave. Wake up.
errg... ungh....
Wake up I say.
Errrrigh.
I thought you said he'd be awake by now?
He should be. Perhaps the dose was too strong. Use the air horn.
*BERRRRRRRRK*
Gah!! What? What?! Where am I?
Why in my clutches of course.

Um....
Could you be a bit more specific?

You are now within my carefully constructed torture, Dave.
A maze from which there is no escape.
But I love mazes.
No! Not this one, anyway.
Around every corner a trap. Through every door a magnificent horror of perfect design.
Sounds delightful.
Silence! Let me finish! ... Now where was I. Oh right. The maze.
Every room is filled with creatures whose only desire is to inflict exquisite suffering.
Sounds like you thought of everything.
Why yes. Yes I did. I have dreamed of this day for an eternity Dungeness Dave.
It's Dungeon Dave actually. But my friends call me Shirley.
Enough!  Now I will watch as you dungeon crawl to your doom.
Sir?
WHAT!!
Um.. Sir, your 11:00 appointment is here.
Oh yes, yes. Of course. Send him in.
Busy?
Now I leave you to your doom Dave.
